item.title: Decompiling, Adding Commands and Recompiling?
item.dc:creator: @ohokay ohokay
item.description:
@ohokay wrote:

Either use reflection to access the fields and methods or use a client where you have access to the source files, and then make it connect to your desired server.

item.title: Decompiling, Adding Commands and Recompiling?
item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

Decompilers do the best possible to re-represent the RAW source form the .class file given to them. They cannot do it perfectly and thus you will have many (possibly hundreds) of errors in the client.java you just generated.

Read full topic
